  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN271">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nīraṟa vaṟiyā nilamutaṟ kalanta</l>
<l>karuṅkura ṉoccik kaṇṇār kurūuttaḻai</l>
<l>melliḻai makaḷi raitaka lalkuṟ</l>
<l>ṟoṭalai yākavuṅ kaṇṭaṉa miṉiyē</l>
<l>veruvaru kurutiyoṭu mayaṅki yuruvukaran</l>
<l>toṟuvāyp paṭṭa teriya lūṉcettup</l>
<l>paruntukoṇ ṭukappayāṅ kaṇṭaṉa</l>
<l>maṟampukaṉ maintaṉ malainta māṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The eye-filling lustrous foliage of the black-eared Nocci</l>
<l>that mixed [its] base with the ground that does not know of the water ceasing,</l>
<l>we have seen it become skirts</l>
<l>on the wonderfully broad hips of tender, jewelled women, and now,</l>
<l>we have seen kites ascend with, thinking [it] flesh,</l>
<l>the garland that found [their] way to ???</l>
<l>[his] form being hidden, mixed up with frightening blood,</l>
<l>because it was worn by the young soldier, rejoicing in boldness.   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
